1.Download Docker 
  For Mac: https://www.docker.com/docker-mac
  For Windows: https://www.docker.com/docker-windows

2.Install Docker on the local machine

3.Install Hadoop Image
  After install Hadoop on the local machine, you need to open the terminal (for mac) or command line (for Windows)
  pull Hadoop image into Docker 
  
  $docker pull kiwenlau/hadoop:1.0
  

4.Create clone storage
	$git clone https://github.com/kiwenlau/hadoop-cluster-docker
	
	For the Mac users, if you meet the error
	
	You can try:
	$xcode-select â€“install
	it will download the xcode for your computer to set up the environment.
	Then try the same code:
	$git clone https://github.com/kiwenlau/hadoop-cluster-docker
 
5.Connect the Internet
	$docker network create --driver=bridge Hadoop
 
6.Running the Container
	$cd hadoop-cluster-docker
	$./start-container.sh
 
	Now, you are in the Linux system, which located in Docker container
	Also you are in the master container
7.	Running the Hadoop
	#./start-hadoop.sh
 
8	Stop the Hadoop
	#stop-all.sh
	


